narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I learned some things about the way digital media interacts with our contemporary culture, and about some of the newer ways in which stories are being told in the digital age.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: very interesting syllabus. there's seems to be a divide between graduate and undergraduate students so the discussion can feel a little awkward sometimes.

I really liked some of the things we watched and read, but the course felt a little unfocused and the discussions tended to drag on a little. I think the thing that would have been the most helpful is if our deadlines had been more solid and our screenings had been mandatory.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I don't think I could recommend this course to another student, just because although the course material was interesting, we didn't learn about it in a particularly interesting way, and the discussions often didn't really get anywhere.
